<p>

<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">
<tr><td class="prompt">created by</td></tr>
<tr><td><a href="/account/profile.php?user_id=92">Benji Fisher</a></td></tr>
<tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
<tr><td class="prompt">script type</td></tr>
<tr><td>utility</td></tr>
<tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
<tr><td class="prompt">description</td></tr>
<tr><td>This file is a collection of Vim functions I have written, many of them in<br>response to questions posted on the vim users' list.&nbsp;&nbsp;They are all reasonably<br>short, so I hope they will be good examples if you are trying to learn how to<br>write your own Vim functions.&nbsp;&nbsp;You may even find some of the functions<br>useful, such as the :Range command and the Mark(), Common(), Count(),<br>GetModelines(), VarTab(), and SmartBS() functions.</td></tr>
<tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
<tr><td class="prompt">install details</td></tr>
<tr><td></td></tr>
<tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
</table>

