    <td class="rowodd" valign="top" width="2000">I added a user configuration section, as discussed on the vim-dev<br>mailing list.&nbsp;&nbsp;With the defaults, most :imap's are not defined, so it<br>is safer to include this in your plugin directory, if you like using any<br>of the commands or functions it defines.&nbsp;&nbsp;Like the rest of the file,<br>the configuration section is meant as an example to be followed.<br>The user should copy this section to a separate file, foo.vimrc .<br><br>I also added functions to save script-local variables in the script<br>file, so they are made persistent.</td>
